Annotate cell identity

This pipeline helps annotate cell identity by visualizing marker genes using UMAP or DOT plot, and by performing reference-based annotation based on ScAClass function.

Option 1: visualize marker genes

Case 1: UMAP visualization

Inputs (Required):
1. -open_markerUMAP yes
2. -script_dir (a script directory downloaded from GitHub: Socrates2/utils/input_other_required_scripts_dir)
3. -impute_gene_mtx (opt_allgenes_impute.activity.rds obtained from Smooth gene accessibility within 5. Prepare gene accessibility)
4. -meta_fl (A meta file obtained from Loading pre-processed data, dimensionality reduction, and clustering)
5. -marker_fl (A marker gene file with a column name called GeneID)
6. -o output_dir (mkdir output_dir)

Optional parameters:
1. -lim_val 0.98 (A lim value of visualizing the markers in UMAP Default: 0.98

Outputs:
1. opt_UMAP_marker.png

Running:

python Socrates2/utils/annotate_cell_identity_using_markers.py
-script_dir Socrates2/utils/input_other_required_scripts_dir
-o output_dir
-open_markerUMAP yes 
-impute_gene_mtx /Path/to/opt_allgenes_impute.activity.rds
-meta_fl /Path/to/meta.txt
-marker_fl /Path/to/marker.txt

Figure 1: example of UMAP plotting

Case 2: Dot plot visualization

Inputs (Required):
1. -open_dotplot yes
2. -script_dir (a script directory downloaded from GitHub: Socrates2/utils/input_other_required_scripts_dir)
3. -impute_gene_mtx (opt_allgenes_impute.activity.rds obtained from from Smooth gene accessibility within 5. Prepare gene accessibility)
4. -meta_fl (A meta file obtained from Loading pre-processed data, dimensionality reduction, and clustering)
5. -gene_tn5_fl (opt_gene_tn5.sparse file obtained from Prepare genes with Tn5 insertions within 5. Prepare gene accessibility
6. -marker_fl (A marker gene file with a column name called GeneID)
7. -o output_dir (mkdir output_dir)

Optional parameters:
1. -clustnm LouvainClusters (Set the cell cluster name within meta file; Default: LouvainClusters.)
2. -dotplotwidth 10 (Define the width of output figure of the dotplot. Default: 10.)
3. -dotplotheight 10 (Define the height of output figure of the dotplot. Default: 10.)
4. -open_only_plot no (Only plot the marker genes. Once we open this step, we need to make sure we firstly ran the whole step completely to obtain the prepared gene file. Users initiate this argument only if they want to just plot other than build up the prepared file. Default: no. 5. -prepared_gene_fl opt_gene_zscore_accprop.rds (A prepared gene file obtained from the firstly running of the whole step.)

Outputs:
1. opt_gene_zscore_accprop.rds
2. opt_dotplot_marker.pdf

Running:

python Socrates2/utils/annotate_cell_identity_using_markers.py
-script_dir Socrates2/utils/input_other_required_scripts_dir
-o output_dir
-open_dotplot yes 
-impute_gene_mtx /Path/to/opt_allgenes_impute.activity.rds
-gene_tn5_fl /Path/to/opt_gene_tn5.sparse
-meta_fl /Path/to/meta.txt
-marker_fl /Path/to/marker.txt

Figure 2: example of marker dot plotting

If users already obtain the file opt_gene_zscore_accprop.rds, users could run the following script other than build up this file again.

python Socrates2/utils/annotate_cell_identity_using_markers.py
-script_dir Socrates2/utils/input_other_required_scripts_dir
-o output_dir
-open_dotplot yes 
-open_only_plot yes
-prepared_gene_fl /Path/to/opt_gene_zscore_accprop.rds 
-marker_fl /Path/to/marker.txt

Option 2: annotate cell identity using marker genes

This step will automatically annotate cell identity based on chromatin accessibility of each marker gene. The outputs will return a single meta file recording predicted cell identity and also include several PNG image files that visualize the average performance of multiple marker genes within single UMAP file.

Inputs (Required):
1. -open_aggregateAnnot yes
2. -script_dir (a script directory downloaded from GitHub: Socrates2/utils/input_other_required_scripts_dir)
3. -gene_acc_mtx (opt_gene_body_accessibility_mtx.rds obtained from Calculate gene accessibility within 5. Prepare gene accessibility)
4. -meta_fl (A meta file obtained from Loading pre-processed data, dimensionality reduction, and clustering)
5. -svd_fl (A svd file obtained from Loading pre-processed data, dimensionality reduction, and clustering)
6. -marker_fl (A marker gene file with a column name called GeneID)

Outputs:
1. opt_annot.meta.txt 2. opt_annot.cell_identities.predicted.png; opt_annot.cell_identities.smooth.png; opt_annot.cell_identities.wknn.png

Running:

python Socrates2/utils/annotate_cell_identity_using_markers.py
-script_dir Socrates2/utils/input_other_required_scripts_dir
-o output_dir
-open_aggregateAnnot yes 
-gene_acc_mtx /Path/to/opt_gene_body_accessibility_mtx.rds
-meta_fl /Path/to/meta.txt
-svd_fl /Path/svd.txt
-marker_fl /Path/to/marker.txt

Option 3: use the reference-based annotation (ScAClass)

The reference-based method is to annotate cell identity using a pre-built gene by cell matrix with each cell identity has been annotated. Currently, this pipeline includes rice (nine organs: axillary bud, early seedling, Seedling, leaf, seminal root, crown root, early seed, late seed, panicle), maize etc. Users need to specify which species and organs they want to use to perform the annotation.

Inputs (Required):
1. -d working_dir (mkdir working_dir)
2. -o output_dir (mkdir output_dir)
3. -script_dir (a script directory downloaded from GitHub: Socrates2/utils/input_other_required_scripts_dir)
4. -train_mtx (input_reference_mtx can be download from Socrates2)
5. -train_meta (input_reference_cell_meta_fl can be download from Socrates2)
6. -unknown_mtx (a matrix called opt_gene_body_accessibility_mtx.rds with cells need to be annotated, which was generated within 5. Prepare gene accessibility)
7. -species (A species name needs to be specified)
8. -organ (A organ name needs to be specified)

Optional parameters:
9. -open_low_mem yes|no (Users could use the low mem to perform the classification by selecting the top variant features of the training dataset. Default: no)
10. -top_ft_num 5000 (Once the low mem open, users could set a top variant ft number. Default: 5000)
11. -clustering_fl Path/to/clustering_fl (Provide a clustering file to build a clustering based annotation)
12. -PC_str 50 (Provide a PC number string used for the embeddings. Default: 50)
13. -Rd_type SVD (Provide a reduction type. Default: SVD)
14. -ML_method SVM (Provide a machine learning method. ScAClass provides Random Forest/RF and Support Vector Machine/SVM. Default: SVM)
15. -SVM_kernel rbf (SVM method provides linear, poly, rbf, sigmoid, precomputed in sklearn. Default: rbf)
16. -open_smote yes (Smote will impute data enabling data balance manner. Default: yes)
17. -running_steps All (Provide running steps to check whether we will run the specific steps. Default: All)

Outputs:
18. opt_final_cell_annotation.txt

python Socrates2/utils/ScAClass.py  
-d working_dir  
-o output_dir  
-script_dir Socrates2/utils/input_other_required_scripts_dir
-train_mtx input_reference_mtx  
-train_meta input_reference_cell_meta_fl  
-unknown_mtx opt_gene_body_accessibility_mtx.rds
-species rice
-organ seedling
